WEBVTT

00:26.027 --> 00:29.028
I can't lose him.

00:31.065 --> 00:35.000
I won't have him committed.
I won't.

00:35.002 --> 00:37.336
No one is suggesting
an institution for dandy.

00:37.338 --> 00:39.905
I refuse to hear
that word uttered

00:39.907 --> 00:41.540
In the same sentence
with his name.

00:41.542 --> 00:43.342
It's an abdication
of responsibility,

00:43.344 --> 00:44.977
Dr. Feinbloom.

00:44.979 --> 00:47.846
Believe me, gloria,
it's the furthest thing

00:47.848 --> 00:49.681
From my mind, but

00:49.683 --> 00:51.750
Apparently not
from from yours.

00:51.752 --> 00:53.986
Dandy's always been
a willful child.

00:56.657 --> 00:58.957
I often thought of him
as a foreigner.

01:00.895 --> 01:03.195
A perfectly groomed
aristocratic boy

01:03.197 --> 01:05.264
Who could play the part

01:05.266 --> 01:07.833
But didn't quite understand
the language.

01:09.070 --> 01:10.702
<i>Because words had a different</i>

01:10.704 --> 01:11.837
<i>Meaning for him.</i>

01:13.941 --> 01:16.141
<i>Particularly the word "no."</i>

01:17.111 --> 01:20.679
<i>"no" was an affront.</i>

01:20.681 --> 01:24.083
<i>"no" was a battle cry.</i>

01:26.887 --> 01:30.889
<i>I had complained about</i>
<i>the cat digging up my azaleas.</i>

01:30.891 --> 01:33.025
<i>So he killed the poor animal.</i>

01:34.061 --> 01:35.761
From that moment on,

01:35.763 --> 01:38.097
I never let dandy
out of my sight.

01:38.099 --> 01:39.465
Of course,
i knew he had to

01:39.467 --> 01:42.067
Socialize with children.

01:42.069 --> 01:44.236
The boy never learned to play.

01:44.238 --> 01:45.571
(child's laugh echoes)

01:45.573 --> 01:47.706
<i>He found a perfect companion</i>

01:47.708 --> 01:49.908
<i>With the gardener's son, emil.</i>

01:49.910 --> 01:51.910
<i>Beautiful little boy.</i>

01:51.912 --> 01:54.746
<i>They would roam the grounds</i>
<i>together, happy as clams.</i>

01:54.748 --> 01:57.483
<i>I relaxed, thinking my vigil</i>

01:57.485 --> 01:59.952
<i>Had become unnecessary.</i>

01:59.954 --> 02:03.088
<i>One day, the boy vanished.</i>
(child's laugh echoes)

02:03.090 --> 02:06.125
They searched
everywhere for him.

02:11.332 --> 02:15.033
But... Emil
was never seen again.

02:17.304 --> 02:20.639
It's time, gloria.
I need to see him.

02:20.641 --> 02:23.008
He would never agree
to psychoanalysis.

02:23.010 --> 02:24.076
Then tell him
it's something else.

02:24.078 --> 02:26.311
I'll clear
my schedule.

02:26.313 --> 02:28.780
Gloria, were
there any

02:28.782 --> 02:31.016
Recent incidents...

02:31.018 --> 02:34.019
(screaming)
aah! Dandy!
Dandy: Mother!

02:34.021 --> 02:36.622
...That triggered this
anxiety about your son?

02:36.624 --> 02:38.690
Just a mother's intuition.

03:50.264 --> 03:52.397
Jimmy:
Ma petite!
(dogs barking)

03:52.399 --> 03:55.601
She's so tiny. She could be
in a hole somewhere,

03:55.603 --> 03:57.536
Screaming, and we wouldn't
hear her, let alone see her.

03:57.538 --> 04:01.106
Petite?
Jimmy: Ma petite.
Where are you?

04:01.108 --> 04:03.408
You head toward that clearing,

04:03.410 --> 04:06.511
I'll hug the riverbed.
Take dimaggio.

04:06.513 --> 04:09.181
Come on, boy.
Come on. Find, find.

04:09.183 --> 04:10.782
Ma petite!

04:10.784 --> 04:13.018
(barking continues)

04:13.020 --> 04:15.187
You got something, boy?
You got something?

04:15.189 --> 04:17.289
Ma petite!
Find it.

04:17.291 --> 04:19.658
Find it.
Ma petite!

04:22.930 --> 04:25.831
(screams)

04:43.951 --> 04:46.018
(gasps)
oh. (cries)

04:49.757 --> 04:52.658
No... No body?

04:52.660 --> 04:54.259
Dell:
Looks like an
animal took her.

04:54.261 --> 04:56.295
Maybe a coyote.

04:56.297 --> 04:59.331
Amazon eve:
Bones and all.

04:59.333 --> 05:03.201
Oh, no.
(crying)

05:12.613 --> 05:14.046
(sobbing):
Oh, no.

05:15.916 --> 05:18.450
Oh, no, no, no,

05:18.452 --> 05:21.586
No, no.
God.

05:21.588 --> 05:25.490
Oh, no, no.

05:25.492 --> 05:27.726
Oh.

05:35.669 --> 05:37.669
Thought you'd be high
as a limehouse whore

05:37.671 --> 05:39.504
By now.

05:42.109 --> 05:44.876
She was too good
for this place, you know?

05:48.549 --> 05:52.818
God put his very own light

05:52.820 --> 05:55.420
Into that little angel.

05:58.492 --> 06:01.993
It was as if he knew

06:01.995 --> 06:04.229
That the world could only handle

06:04.231 --> 06:07.699
A tiny bit of his love at once.

06:10.070 --> 06:12.204
Well, come on.

06:12.206 --> 06:14.272
Oh.

06:17.144 --> 06:18.877
Oh, edna.
Looks like

06:18.879 --> 06:20.746
You have already taken steps

06:20.748 --> 06:23.081
To dull your pain.

06:23.083 --> 06:24.549
A woman's entitled

06:24.551 --> 06:27.152
To a little nip or two

06:27.154 --> 06:29.988
On a dark night of the soul.

06:29.990 --> 06:32.557
Sit. Eat.

06:34.528 --> 06:37.095
We will mourn her.

06:37.097 --> 06:39.731
Christmas is canceled.

06:39.733 --> 06:41.800
I made mock turtle soup.

06:45.939 --> 06:48.507
That was quite a show
you put on in that tent.

06:50.244 --> 06:52.043
Regular joan fontaine.

06:52.045 --> 06:55.914
I've seen you bring a
full house to their feet,

06:55.916 --> 06:59.017
But you have never been better
than you were tonight.

06:59.019 --> 07:02.921
You have got it, elsa mars.

07:04.091 --> 07:06.691
The sobs over ma petite.

07:06.693 --> 07:10.228
Clutching her bloody dress--
that was a nice touch.

07:10.230 --> 07:14.032
Bit of a house
note, but damn...

07:14.034 --> 07:16.835
I almost believed
you meant it.

07:19.139 --> 07:20.372
(grunts)

07:20.374 --> 07:22.207
How dare you?

07:23.310 --> 07:26.511
She was my most precious one.

07:28.215 --> 07:31.483
All that's precious to you
is the roar of the crowd.

07:32.786 --> 07:35.420
And god forbid
someone comes along

07:35.422 --> 07:38.023
And steals your spotlight.
(drumroll, applause)

07:41.962 --> 07:45.063
(whooping, cheering)

08:06.987 --> 08:08.787
You know,

08:08.789 --> 08:12.190
I have seen the way whiskey
can ravage the mind,

08:12.192 --> 08:14.359
But you come in here tonight

08:14.361 --> 08:16.628
And you accuse me of what?

08:16.630 --> 08:20.165
Of killing innocence
itself? Huh?

08:20.167 --> 08:22.000
Get out!

08:22.002 --> 08:24.035
14 years.

08:24.037 --> 08:25.837
I've brought you your tray,

08:25.839 --> 08:27.873
Washed your hair,

08:27.875 --> 08:29.374
Listened to all those
tall tales

08:29.376 --> 08:31.209
About what was,

08:31.211 --> 08:33.278
What could have been.

08:35.616 --> 08:38.617
I heard those stories...

08:38.619 --> 08:41.286
Ten times over, elsa.

08:41.288 --> 08:43.188
I know you

08:43.190 --> 08:45.257
Better than you know yourself.

08:47.394 --> 08:51.062
I've always wondered why,

08:51.064 --> 08:55.166
When i loved you so much,

08:55.168 --> 08:59.004
It gave me such pain
to be around you.

08:59.006 --> 09:02.874
How when i'd leave here
at night i'd just...

09:02.876 --> 09:05.110
Felt like i lost something.

09:06.680 --> 09:09.014
A woman shouldn't dread...

09:09.016 --> 09:12.317
Spending time
with her best friend.

09:12.319 --> 09:15.687
Why'd i feel so uneasy?

09:15.689 --> 09:17.822
Now i know.

09:21.762 --> 09:22.894
Who am i,

09:22.896 --> 09:26.531
If not your savior, huh?

09:26.533 --> 09:28.833
And this is the thanks.

09:28.835 --> 09:31.169
You call me a murderer

09:31.171 --> 09:34.005
On a night
when i have already lost...

09:34.007 --> 09:36.575
So much?

09:38.111 --> 09:40.078
Damn you for this!

09:40.080 --> 09:42.981
Goddamn you for this!

09:43.917 --> 09:45.984
Damn you!

09:48.455 --> 09:50.589
You were our mother.

09:50.591 --> 09:53.592
There's people around here
who never even met theirs.

09:53.594 --> 09:55.126
You understand...

09:55.128 --> 09:58.964
The pain of being rejected
by your own mother?

09:58.966 --> 10:00.966
Of course you do.

10:00.968 --> 10:03.034
That's how you
sucked us all in here.

10:03.036 --> 10:07.205
Come one, come all,
suckle at elsa's bosom.

10:07.207 --> 10:08.473
All are welcome.

10:08.475 --> 10:10.041
Just don't ask for top billing.

10:11.278 --> 10:13.411
Enough of this.

10:13.413 --> 10:16.047
I have killed no one.

10:16.049 --> 10:18.149
What about the twins?

10:18.151 --> 10:19.718
I stood right there.

10:19.720 --> 10:22.253
I heard you talking
to that fella from hollywood.

10:22.255 --> 10:24.389
Wouldn't it be a better solution
if they could be

10:24.391 --> 10:26.091
Quietly and easily relieved

10:26.093 --> 10:27.659
Of their misery?

10:27.661 --> 10:28.760
What are you saying?

10:28.762 --> 10:30.395
A mercy killing.

10:30.397 --> 10:31.997
Elsa: Oh, that's
quite a solution.

10:31.999 --> 10:34.466
And you, you didn't even blink.

10:34.468 --> 10:36.901
"quite a solution,"

10:36.903 --> 10:38.336
You called it.

10:38.338 --> 10:40.805
I died when i heard you
say that.

10:42.676 --> 10:44.743
You killed me dead.

10:49.516 --> 10:52.083
It was a turn of phrase.

10:52.085 --> 10:53.084
(scoffs)

10:53.086 --> 10:54.285
But i will be judged

10:54.287 --> 10:56.621
On my actions,

10:56.623 --> 10:58.056
And not on my words.

10:59.760 --> 11:02.127
So now i am
going to go out,

11:02.129 --> 11:03.862
I'm going to find
those twins,

11:03.864 --> 11:05.997
I'm going to bring
them back here,

11:05.999 --> 11:08.933
So they can pronounce
my innocence to you

11:08.935 --> 11:10.335
One more time!

11:10.337 --> 11:12.003
No way.

11:12.005 --> 11:14.305
No, i made sure

11:14.307 --> 11:16.007
They were safe somewhere

11:16.009 --> 11:17.342
Away from you.

11:17.344 --> 11:19.210
My, my.

11:19.212 --> 11:21.279
Well, you got me, copper.

11:21.281 --> 11:23.014
Huh? (chuckles)

11:23.016 --> 11:25.016
Guilty as charged.

11:26.787 --> 11:29.187
Yes, i wanted them to be gone.

11:30.557 --> 11:32.057
But i never hurt anyone.

11:32.059 --> 11:35.226
I wanted to be rid of them.

11:35.228 --> 11:37.996
Put them on a bus to tampa.

11:37.998 --> 11:41.733
Although, for me, death would be
preferable to tampa.

11:42.703 --> 11:44.669
And i will no longer suffer

11:44.671 --> 11:48.239
Your insults and your insanity!

11:50.877 --> 11:54.879
Apparently, i have lost
two old friends tonight.

11:54.881 --> 11:57.115
No.

12:00.921 --> 12:04.089
(laughing)

12:04.091 --> 12:06.391
Oh, ethel...

12:06.393 --> 12:11.596
I am just like the rest
of my children.

12:11.598 --> 12:16.367
I love you
because i understand you.

12:16.369 --> 12:19.237
You think you know me, hmm?

12:21.575 --> 12:24.442
You... Don't know me at all.

12:26.079 --> 12:29.080
(speaking german)

12:29.082 --> 12:32.851
<i>A sweet young soldier</i>
<i>with a kind heart found me</i>

12:32.853 --> 12:35.086
<i>And brought me to my safety.</i>

12:35.088 --> 12:37.956
<i>His name was massimo dolcefino.</i>

12:37.958 --> 12:40.925
(speaking german)

12:40.927 --> 12:43.928
<i>He found his fame</i>
<i>in the first world war</i>

12:43.930 --> 12:46.131
<i>When grenades became</i>
<i>the great terror,</i>

12:46.133 --> 12:49.234
<i>Separating soldiers</i>
<i>from their limbs.</i>

12:49.236 --> 12:54.906
<i>With an almost unlimited supply</i>
<i>of clients for his prosthetics,</i>

12:54.908 --> 12:58.543
<i>Massimo elevated</i>
<i>his craft into art.</i>

12:58.545 --> 13:00.578
<i>But after the war,</i>

13:00.580 --> 13:04.315
<i>He fell on hard times.</i>

13:06.286 --> 13:08.787
(groans softly)

13:19.399 --> 13:22.600
(panting)

13:22.602 --> 13:25.136
(speaks quietly
in german)

13:26.840 --> 13:28.006
No.

13:31.344 --> 13:34.012
No.

13:34.014 --> 13:36.581
(speaking german)

13:51.431 --> 13:53.498
<i>Massimo emigrated to germany</i>

13:53.500 --> 13:55.934
<i>To work in the movies</i>

13:55.936 --> 14:00.004
<i>As a sculptor, a prop maker.</i>

14:02.008 --> 14:04.309
<i>And it was there</i>

14:04.311 --> 14:07.612
<i>He met his greatest challenge.</i>

14:07.614 --> 14:10.515
<i>Me.</i>

14:29.035 --> 14:30.969
(laughter echoing)

14:32.239 --> 14:35.373
So now you see.

14:35.375 --> 14:37.909
Why didn't you tell me all this?

14:39.512 --> 14:41.679
Why'd you keep it a secret
from me?

14:41.681 --> 14:43.915
I was humiliated, ashamed.

14:43.917 --> 14:47.585
Can't you see
how deep it is?

14:47.587 --> 14:51.589
Ethel... Put the gun away.

14:51.591 --> 14:54.158
No.

14:56.096 --> 14:59.831
Curtain comes down tonight.

14:59.833 --> 15:03.268
Do you think the others
will cover for your murder?

15:04.504 --> 15:07.305
The last bullet's for me.

15:10.043 --> 15:12.510
You broke my heart in two, elsa.

15:14.014 --> 15:17.115
I loved you.

15:17.117 --> 15:19.684
I gave my life to you.

15:19.686 --> 15:22.186
I defended you.

15:24.090 --> 15:27.091
For me, the only
pure things

15:27.093 --> 15:30.128
In the world was
little ma petite,

15:30.130 --> 15:33.564
And my love and
dedication for you.

15:33.566 --> 15:35.533
Now they're both gone.

15:35.535 --> 15:37.135
And jimmy, your own son?

15:37.137 --> 15:38.803
He'll survive.

15:38.805 --> 15:41.372
I left him a letter.
It's in the caravan.

15:41.374 --> 15:44.409
And the rest
of our children?

15:44.411 --> 15:47.712
Your descent into madness
can cross over my corpse,

15:47.714 --> 15:50.315
But you will not kill
my children.

15:50.317 --> 15:52.150
They are innocents.

15:52.152 --> 15:54.786
It's all over, elsa.

15:56.323 --> 15:59.324
For all of us.

15:59.326 --> 16:01.960
No one's innocent anymore.

16:05.465 --> 16:07.465
So be it.

16:07.467 --> 16:09.867
(laughs)

16:11.104 --> 16:13.504
But first...

16:13.506 --> 16:17.976
One last schnapps
for the road?

16:17.978 --> 16:19.410
Hmm?

16:19.412 --> 16:22.914
A toast to our history.

16:28.822 --> 16:31.356
Go on.

16:41.968 --> 16:45.403
We've never shared a drink
before, have we?

16:51.978 --> 16:54.979
I'm sorry, you won't be going

16:54.981 --> 16:57.148
To hollywood, elsa.
So, you won't be there

16:57.150 --> 16:58.950
With me.

17:12.832 --> 17:14.365
Is she hurt?
Not that
i could see.

17:14.367 --> 17:15.867
That richard spencer
fella found her

17:15.869 --> 17:18.236
Out by the ferris wheel,
blubbering.

17:20.006 --> 17:22.673
(maggie crying)
maggie?

17:22.675 --> 17:24.976
Oh, jimmy!

17:24.978 --> 17:26.644
What? What happened?

17:26.646 --> 17:29.213
That is what we are trying
to determine.

17:31.017 --> 17:33.151
I was out in the woods,

17:33.153 --> 17:36.854
Picking flowers for
ma petite's memorial grave.

17:36.856 --> 17:38.756
(car engine approaching,
crashing)

17:38.758 --> 17:41.159
<i>There was a crash.</i>

17:41.161 --> 17:42.560
<i>I went to see what it was,</i>

17:42.562 --> 17:45.563
<i>And there was a car,</i>
<i>and in the car...</i>

17:45.565 --> 17:48.066
(gasps, screams)

17:48.068 --> 17:50.268
I'm sorry, jimmy.
It was your mother.

17:50.270 --> 17:52.070
She's dead.
Elsa (gasps):
What?

17:52.072 --> 17:55.273
Not ethel. Oh, no,
that can't be.

17:55.275 --> 17:57.942
She was in an accident?

17:57.944 --> 17:59.010
It wasn't an accident.

17:59.012 --> 18:00.912
I think she killed herself.

18:00.914 --> 18:03.114
(people gasping)
shit!

18:03.116 --> 18:05.450
Come on.
Elsa:
Suicide?

18:05.452 --> 18:07.752
Oh, dear, no.

18:07.754 --> 18:09.220
Oh, but why?!

18:09.222 --> 18:11.222
She was sick.

18:11.224 --> 18:13.124
In a lot of
pain, too.

18:13.126 --> 18:16.094
No. My mom wasn't sick.

18:16.096 --> 18:18.062
Dell:
She was, though, son.

18:18.064 --> 18:20.098
No.
She told me so herself.

18:20.100 --> 18:21.766
(crying):
No.

18:21.768 --> 18:23.601
Guess she wanted
to go out on her own terms.

18:23.603 --> 18:27.138
Elsa:
Oh. My god.

18:27.140 --> 18:29.740
Where is she?
Take me to her.

18:29.742 --> 18:31.375
Desiree:
Her head's come off?

18:31.377 --> 18:33.978
Jesus.

18:33.980 --> 18:35.947
How hard did she hit that tree?

18:35.949 --> 18:38.216
(people gasping and exclaiming)

18:39.152 --> 18:40.751
Look!

18:40.753 --> 18:43.054
Oh!
She must have
wrapped this chain

18:43.056 --> 18:44.922
Around that tree, and then
wrapped it around her neck,

18:44.924 --> 18:46.958
Then hit the gas.

18:46.960 --> 18:48.960
I guess she wanted it
to be quick.

18:48.962 --> 18:50.094
Oh!

18:50.096 --> 18:52.430
Oh,<i> mein</i> god in heaven!

18:52.432 --> 18:53.731
Why?!

18:53.733 --> 18:55.433
What do you mean, "why?"

18:55.435 --> 18:58.836
Why can't we just hang her in
her caravan and be done with it?

18:58.838 --> 19:00.938
Because you chucked a knife
through her eye socket.

19:00.940 --> 19:02.607
Oh, god.
That's why.

19:02.609 --> 19:04.142
(groans)

19:04.144 --> 19:06.644
This accident is gonna
cover a whole host of sins,

19:06.646 --> 19:09.981
All of them yours.

19:09.983 --> 19:12.150
Where's your sense
of drama?
This is not theater!

19:12.152 --> 19:13.584
That's exactly what it is.

19:13.586 --> 19:15.753
This is a magic trick.
We have to divert

19:15.755 --> 19:18.689
The attention of the audience in
order to pull off the illusion.

19:18.691 --> 19:20.458
Oh, my god.

19:20.460 --> 19:24.095
No, don't.
My god, what have i done?

19:24.097 --> 19:26.931
(crying):
Oh, ethel.

19:26.933 --> 19:28.599
But you understand.

19:28.601 --> 19:30.168
I had to kill her.

19:30.170 --> 19:32.036
I had to protect
my precious angels.

19:32.038 --> 19:33.604
Horseshit.

19:33.606 --> 19:35.873
You had to
protect yourself.

19:35.875 --> 19:37.642
But you don't...

19:37.644 --> 19:40.044
Why are you doing
this for me, huh?

19:40.046 --> 19:41.979
Tell me, why are you
doing this for me?!

19:41.981 --> 19:45.483
This... This... This is what
we do in hollywood.

19:45.485 --> 19:47.051
You are my client.

19:47.053 --> 19:49.654
I have an obligation
to-to protect you,

19:49.656 --> 19:51.055
Protect your career.

19:51.057 --> 19:53.057
You have a destiny,

19:53.059 --> 19:55.993
Written in the stars,
to be a star.

19:55.995 --> 19:58.996
You're gonna win
an oscar one day.

19:58.998 --> 20:00.898
Do you really think so?

20:00.900 --> 20:03.167
I do. I do.

20:03.169 --> 20:05.102
(engine revving,
